divs: Sighting DetailsI was at a classic car event at the Ford Plant in mid October 1996. A brillant oval shapped object dropped down through the clouds. The light was so bright it was hard to see. It was the size of a Cessna and was 2-3 miles away. It remained stationary for 1 minute. It started to whobble downward and then ascended back into the cloud coverage.
Summary: A brillant oval shapped object descended into view. The light was so brillant it was difficult to see.
